    <mxCell id="notes" value="Application Notes &amp; Metadata&#10;&#10;&#8226; CTR (Project Scissors): analyses US Cash Transaction Report data; delivers metrics, dashboards &amp; reports. New card/application in the Citi Risk &amp; Controls (CRC) portal.&#10;&#8226; CSI 176042 (OPEN ISSUE: governance directive may require a NEW CSI for the new app/backend/schema &#8211; pending confirmation).&#10;&#8226; Hosting: OpenShift (Citi PaaS). Web tier: Apache. Backend: Java. Frontend: React.&#10;&#8226; Source: US Retail Cash Transaction Reporting (CSI 165802) &#8211; system of record, existing US system. Integration via NDM (file drop); justified because source is a legacy SoR with no manual intervention and automated, traceable lineage.&#10;&#8226; Volume ~8,000 CTRs/month; monthly feed; 10-year retention (US compliance).&#10;&#8226; Data lineage documented in Data Catalog. No downstream apps; APIs exposed for dashboard only.&#10;&#8226; Cognos reports (separate team) are replicated in React; Cognos is not integrated.&#10;&#8226; Acronyms: NDM=Network Data Mover (managed file transfer); CRC=Citi Risk &amp; Controls; ICRM=Independent Compliance Risk Mgmt; ORAAS=Oracle RAC as a Service; SSO=Single Sign-On; CTR=Cash Transaction Report; SoR=System of Record." style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;shape=mxgraph.basic.document;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#D6B656;dashed=1;dashPattern=12 12;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" vertex="1" parent="1">
      <mxGeometry x="640" y="1210" width="960" height="370" as="geometry"/>
    </mxCell>
